  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Samuel May, Jr., asks Maria Weston Chapman to write a notice in the Standard of John Bishop Estlin&apos;s &quot;Brief Notice of American Slavery, etc.&quot; [The work referred to is A Brief Notice of American Slavery, and the Abolition Movement., by John Bishop Estlin, 1846.] In consideration of his own intimate correspondence with Mr. Estlin, Samuel May wants someone less biased than himself to write the review. He was pleased to see E. Quincy&apos;s notice of the tract in the latest issue of the Liberator.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The letterhead on page one of this manuscript consists of an engraving (print) depicting a slave woman in chains, with the caption: &quot;Am I not a woman and a sister?&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
